The paper deals with identifying users in an online recommender system based on their ratings, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of subspace clustering for identifying composite accounts is a clustering technique, which falls under the data mining (cs.DB) sub-category. The paper also discusses privacy concerns, which falls under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the potential uses for personalized recommendation fall under the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
